#select the index of 2010 and 2019
hdrtable_2 <- hdrtable %>%
  dplyr::select("iso3","country","gii_2010","gii_2019")

#mew column with the average of 2010 and 2019
gender_inequality <- hdrtable_2 %>%
  mutate(differen_gender_inequality=gii_2010-gii_2019) 

#top of data
slice_head(gender_inequality, n=5)
## # A tibble: 5 × 5
##   iso3  country     gii_2010 gii_2019 differen_gender_inequality
##   <chr> <chr>          <dbl>    <dbl>                      <dbl>
## 1 AFG   Afghanistan    0.707    0.676                     0.0310
## 2 ALB   Albania        0.192    0.131                     0.061 
## 3 DZA   Algeria        0.517    0.397                     0.12  
## 4 AND   Andorra       NA       NA                        NA     
## 5 AGO   Angola         0.554    0.533                     0.0210
#convert iso3 to iso2
gender_inequality_2 <- gender_inequality %>%
  filter(!is.na(gii_2010))%>%
  mutate(ISO=countrycode(iso3,"iso3c","iso2c"))
## Warning: There was 1 warning in `mutate()`.
## ℹ In argument: `ISO = countrycode(iso3, "iso3c", "iso2c")`.

#merge the data
gender_inequalty_world <- world%>%
  left_join(.,
            gender_inequality_2,
            by="ISO")
